messages.message: Extraction issues reported by a commercial account (Mantle). The model was able to return correct results with prompt "What is the distributions amount?" under both reasoning and extraction mode. But with just "distributions," it returns "no value found." Any idea why this might be happening? @lydia @Nikolaos Kofinas

Also any suggestions on the right prompts to get values for I*, N*, V*...or numbers under/next to Other Information? Tried using prompts such as "return the number next to Other Information" but it didn't work.
can you provide the sample document from the screenshots?
i’m able to get the keys and values under “Other information” using the list data type
Let me know if this works for you.
Another challenge they had is to get the values out for Profit/Loss/Capital Beginning
when i digitized this document, i can see it didn’t digitize the part under “20 other information’ very well
this prompt seems to work for “Profit/Loss/Capital Beginning”

One last issue that the customer reported is that they are seeing different results while they didn't change any prompt or edit any field. Have we seen such inconsistencies else where? What might be causing this to happen?
@Bastiane is there an email chain you can forward to us? where are you getting this feedback?
also, if they didn't change any prompts or edit any fields, how did they get different results? I  don't think we allow rerunning if nothing changes

Just forwarded the email to you. They cloned the project over when they started commercial trial and the results are different between community and commercial account. I now have access to their project. And I'm seeing different extraction results than the screenshot they sent me too (see above screenshots)
Can you let me use your account? or add me as well?
@Serena I reproduced the no value found! here's the har
while extraction was running, i clicked "Run" on a clean line. The extraction then immediately stopped and showed "No value found"

hmm ok i can't reproduce it again, so it's not very easy to do so :disappointed: I also thought the cached "No value found" might be why the user keeps seeing it, but I think we always rerun "No value founds" when we reload the page right? so it's also confusing they are consistently seeing it
